fallback.description: A fallback function that is triggered when the contract receives ether without data.

proxyType.description: Returns the type of the proxy.

isDepositable.description: Returns whether the contract is depositable.

implementation.description: Returns the address of the implementation contract.

kernel.description: Returns the address of the kernel contract.

constructor.description: Initializes the contract with the specified kernel address, application ID, and initialization payload.

ProxyDeposit.description: Emitted when a deposit is made to the proxy.
